        <abstract> 
<p>Responds to JD’s letter [<hi rend="doubleUnderline">2944</hi>]. Would like to know whether bees extract pollen from within the indusium of <hi rend="italic">Leschenaultia</hi>. He suspects they brush over and partly open the indusium while sucking nectar from the flower.</p> 
            <p>Asks also about malvaceous plant that set seed although its flower never opened.</p> 
<p>Has been watching the achenia of the plant sent by JD and, if Hooker agrees, will publish a note on it ["Achenia of <hi rend="italic">Pumilio argyrolepis</hi>", <hi rend="italic">Collected papers</hi> 2: 36–8].</p> 
        </abstract>
